        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(update): continue after package doctor warnings",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Downgrade package post-install `openclaw doctor --fix` only for the dedicated exit code, a normally terminated child, and a valid typed deferred-configured-plugin-repair advisory after package verification.\n- Keep unknown nonzero exits, killed/timed-out/signaled doctor runs, malformed or missing results, and the non-converging generic update path blocking.\n- Surface advisory doctor diagnostics in progress and summaries, then continue through mandatory post-core plugin convergence before restart.\n- Scope advisory details to repairs explicitly deferred by doctor so successful unrelated changes, including stale bundled-record cleanup, do not produce false exit-86 warnings.\n- Place the advisory sidecar under OpenClaw's secured preferred temp root.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Focused current-head Vitest proof: 355 tests across five shards.\n- `pnpm check` (preflight guards, prod/extension typecheck, lint, policy guards) passed.\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD` passed.\n- `git merge-tree --write-tree upstream/main HEAD` completed conflict-free.\n- Persisted Kepler autoreview passed in repair-only local mode and full branch mode.\n- Real package update proof remains from a packed ancestor branch tarball with a Node preload hook that forces only the post-install doctor child to return the typed advisory exit.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: The `openclaw update` CLI package path continues past post-install doctor only for the dedicated exit code, a normally terminated child, and a valid typed deferred-configured-plugin-repair advisory. The advisory is now emitted only when the repair producer explicitly reports deferred repair details; unrelated successful doctor changes do not become advisory exits. The package updater then runs mandatory post-core plugin convergence before restart. The non-converging generic `runGatewayUpdate` path keeps post-install doctor nonzero results blocking and does not participate in the advisory IPC contract.\n\nReal environment tested: The prior packed-package macOS update proof remains from ancestor head 377924d03129cc97b094c1d2681148e37487e5f0. Current head b725d941a5d943b77820d256370eb5352bd30e01 was tested in the isolated macOS PR worktree with Node 24.14.0 against upstream/main ded3a930587638d4014442db133e6d2cb40ab279.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```sh\nenv -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_KIND -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_MARKER -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_VERSION -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_MANAGED_ENV_KEYS -u OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_SERVICE_PID -u OPENCLAW_LAUNCHD_LABEL -u OPENCLAW_SYSTEMD_UNIT -u OPENCLAW_WINDOWS_TASK_NAME -u OPENCLAW_WRAPPER PATH=/Users/jason/.nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/bin:$PATH OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=2 OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-pr-91586-vitest-final node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/update-runner.test.ts src/cli/update-cli.test.ts src/infra/package-update-steps.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/release-configured-plugin-installs.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/missing-configured-plugin-install.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/update.test.ts\npnpm check\ngit diff --check upstream/main...HEAD\ngit merge-tree --write-tree upstream/main HEAD\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --codex-bin /Users/jason/.codex/openclaw-pr-autopilot/bin/codex-persist-sessions --model codex=kepler-alpha --thinking codex=high\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main --codex-bin /Users/jason/.codex/openclaw-pr-autopilot/bin/codex-persist-sessions --model codex=kepler-alpha --thinking codex=high\nnode scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run -- env OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 corepack pnpm check:changed\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: The focused suite passed 355 tests across five Vitest shards, including the CLI advisory continuation path, shared advisory classifier, explicit deferred-repair producer result, false-advisory regression for unrelated bundled-record cleanup, configured-plugin doctor flow, generic update runner, and gateway error/no-restart contract. `pnpm check` passed preflight guards, prod/extension typechecks, lint, and policy guards. `git diff --check` was clean. The current-main merge simulation was conflict-free and produced tree 50255fac7a2535f2a8b4ac7b9cd331724ff6d175. Fresh persisted repair-only and full-branch Kepler autoreviews both reported no accepted/actionable findings and judged the patch correct.\n\nCopied live output excerpt from the real packed-package updater run on ancestor 377924d03129cc97b094c1d2681148e37487e5f0:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"mode\": \"npm\",\n  \"doctor\": {\n    \"name\": \"openclaw doctor\",\n    \"exitCode\": 86,\n    \"advisory\": { \"kind\": \"package-post-install-doctor\" },\n    \"stderrTail\": \"Skipped package-manager repair for configured plugin discord during package update; rerun openclaw doctor --fix after the update completes.\"\n  },\n  \"postUpdatePluginsStatus\": \"warning\"\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The typed advisory gate authorizes only the intended recoverable doctor result in the CLI package updater, and the advisory producer now distinguishes actual deferred repair details from unrelated successful repair changes. Unknown exits, missing or malformed results, killed runs, signals, and timeouts remain blocking. The sidecar path uses OpenClaw's secured preferred temp root and passes the current temp-path policy guard.\n\nWhat was not tested: Current head did not rerun the packed-package real update or a managed gateway restart. Crabbox/Testbox did not execute because the Azure coordinator first returned HTTP 500, then timed out after ten minutes without granting an execution lease. No Mantis lane was required, and no live or protected channel was touched.\n",
